  "texts": [
    "We note that although Q does not commute with the currents J(z), K(z) and S(z), it does commute with all of the zero modes of J a (z) and K a (z) (the bosonic isometries) and half 7 of the zero modes of S αA± (z).We now have an extended worldsheet symmetry algebra generated by T, Q and Z.",
    "The T and Q part of this algebra looks somewhat like a simplified W -algebra,[L m, L n] = (m -n)L m+n + c 12 (m 3 -m)δ m+n,0, [L m, Q n] = (2m -n)Q m+n, [Q m, Q n] = 0,where c is the central charge.",
    "8 By \"simplified\" we simply mean that the weight 3 generator commutes with itself, which is not generically the case for W -algebras.",
    "The symmetry generated by Q will play a starring role in what follows, whilst little attention will be given to the scaling symmetry of Z.",
    "This scaling symmetry is only present in the k = 1 string for the free field realisation and not in the hybrid formalism."
  ],
